      <section id="id1165515546540">
        <title>To understand and use singular and plural forms of ordinary nouns [LO 6.4.1]</title>
        <para id="id1165506767234">4. Most nouns (naming words) have plural forms. That means that the words indicate that there is more than one of the things that are being named, for example:</para>
        <para id="id1165509901760">one planet - many planets</para>
        <para id="id1165506790488">one country - many countries</para>
        <para id="id1165515828560">one animal - many animals</para>
        <para id="id1165510165393">one river - many rivers</para>
        <para id="id1165509130019">one meeting - many meetings</para>
      </section>
